---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Contact UseToolEasy — Support and Feedback"
  description="Contact page for UseToolEasy. Use it to report issues, request features, or send feedback about the shared-domain dev and media tools site."
  canonicalPath="/contact/"
>
  <section class="py-12 lg:py-20">
    <div class="section-shell">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-zinc-900 sm:text-5xl">Contact</h1>
        
        <div class="mt-8 rounded-2xl border border-zinc-200/80 bg-white p-6 sm:p-10 shadow-sm">
          <div class="prose-copy text-zinc-600">
            <p>If you want to report a broken workflow, request a new utility, or share feedback about the grouped-site model, use the maintainer contact route below.</p>
            
            <ul class="my-6 space-y-2">
              <li>Support email: <strong>[replace-with-real-support-email@example.com]</strong></li>
              <li>Expected use: bug reports, feature requests, trust/privacy questions, and deployment issues</li>
              <li>Honest note: this is an independent tool suite, so response times may vary</li>
            </ul>
            
            <p>Before public launch, replace the placeholder support email with a real inbox. Do not leave fake or dead contact information on the live site.</p>
            
            <h2 class="mt-10 text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-zinc-900">What to include in a support message</h2>
            <p>If a tool breaks, include the route name, your browser, what you pasted into the tool, and what result you expected. For privacy questions, mention which route you were using and whether the issue involved JSON, text, regex, SQL, or local media processing.</p>
            <p>If you are requesting a new feature, say whether it should live on an existing child page or whether it deserves a new route. That distinction matters for grouped-site SEO and for keeping the information architecture clean.</p>
            <p>This contact page exists as part of the site-wide trust layer. It is not just there for an audit checkbox; it should be a realistic route for support, feedback, and privacy concerns once the placeholder details are replaced.</p>
            
            <h2 class="mt-10 text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-zinc-900">Reasonable response expectations</h2>
            <p>Because this grouped site is maintained as an independent tools suite, urgent enterprise-style support is not implied. If a report affects privacy, corrupted output, or a route that no longer loads, those issues should be prioritized first. Cosmetic feedback and feature ideas can follow after the core workflow is stable.</p>
            <p>A useful contact route lowers trust friction. When someone lands on this page from the footer, they should be able to understand how to report an issue, what kind of response is realistic, and how the grouped site handles privacy-related questions across all child routes.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
